INSERT INTO `investments` VALUES (1,'2018-06-17 22:08:55','Geo Visual Analytics','http://www.geovisual-analytics.com','/img/portfolio/gva.png','<h6><font face=\"Verdana\">GeoVisual Analytics (“GeoVisual”) has developed an Artificial Intelligence (AI) based computer image analysis technology to enable high-value crop growers and processors to know when and where to harvest, improving profitability and reducing costs. Using systematic monitoring of fields with airplanes, drones, and mobile phones, GeoVisual applies its AI algorithms to analyze crop maturity, health, and predicted yields. GeoVisual provides this information via a SaaS platform with an annual subscription, selling directly to large producers and to smaller ones through grower associations. The company is currently targeting the largest U.S. producers of specialty crops with business centers in CA, Western US, and in Mexico.&nbsp;</font></h6>','Jeff, Charles','','','Agriculture, AI, Software','Boulder, CO','0 of 3','Jeff Orrey, Andrew McGregor, Joe Kelsay','','','',0.00,1.67,80.00,20.00,49999.96,49999.96,0.00,79325.00,1.50,0.00,'COMPLETE'),(2,'2018-06-17 22:08:55','Swimlane','swimlane.com','img/portfolio/sl.png','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Swimlane is a leader in security automation and orchestration (SAO), recognized by both Gartner and Forrester for providing a platform that empowers organizations to manage, respond to and neutralize cyber threats with the adaptability, efficiency and speed necessary to combat constantly growing and rapidly evolving cyber threat. By automating time-intensive, manual processes and operational workflows, and delivering powerful, consolidated analytics, real time dashboards, and reporting from across your security infrastructure, Swimlane maximizes the incident response capabilities of overburdened and understaffed security operations.</span></h6>','Cody Cornell, CEO Jorge Esguerra, CFO Steve Shaw, SVP of Sales Kevin Broughton, VP of Marketing David Pack, VP of Field Ops Chris Stimmel, VP of Engineering','','','Cyber Security, Enterprise Software','Louisville, CO','0 of 3','David Amsler, Cody Cornell, Brian Kafenbaum','','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Swimlane was founded in 2014 and is led by a management team that is rich in cyber security operations and product expertise, with a proven track record of creating, marketing and selling high growth enterprise security solutions, as well as building highly effective security operations programs at scale. In December of 2016, Swimlane completed a Series A financing of $3.3 million with angel investors with strategic expertise in cybersecurity. Additionally, in December 2017 Swimlane completed a follow-on investment of $1.35 million from current investors and is currently seeking to complete an additional financing round to support an expansion of its direct sales team, marketing capacity, and operations. Swimlane’s platform has been validated in the marketplace through a number of customer production deployments across several vertical and industries, including multiple Fortune 500 enterprises, large federal institutions like the DHS, and large domestic and multinational financial services organizations.</span></h6>','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Security Automation and Orchestration is a growing industry. There is high competition in advanced AI-based threat detection software but not many options for security analysts to automate their most important tasks. Security analysts investigate less than 1% of the threat alerts they receive per day. Swimlane has greatly increa﻿sed the number of security software integrations for automation. Their YOY Growth is at 114% and their revenue tripled in two years since inception. Splunk has recently acquired Phantom for $350M to target SOAR domain and made the space very attractive for acquisitions. </span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">﻿</span></h6>',0.00,0.16,80.00,20.00,50000.00,50000.00,0.00,50000.00,1.00,0.00,'COMPLETE'),(4,'2018-06-17 22:08:55','PharmaJet','www.pharmajet.com','img/portfolio/pj.png','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">PharmaJet has developed user-friendly, inexpensive device platforms for fluid injection into the body without a needle. Able to compete with traditional needle-syringe delivery, which inherently poses costly needle-stick, re-use and pass-along disease issues, PharmaJet</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">s devices have been optimized for vaccine administration, a 2.8B annual immunization market growing in excess of the 140m annual birth cohort. Unique in the field of jet injection because of its ability to reach target tissues accurately and comfortably, PharmaJet has unique scientific claims and wide regulatory clearances. </span></h6>','Heather','','<p>Healthios is PharmaJet\'s partner for IPO process and the valuation is done by them.&nbsp;</p>','Medical Device, Pharma','Golden, CO','0 of 5','Ron Lowy, Jeffrey A. Jordan, Heather Callender-Potters, Chris Cappello','','Please checkout the attached summary.','<p>This is a much later stage investment and out of the strategy but the exit path appeared much shorter as they have enormous amount of traction and heading toward IPO path. This is truly a short exit opportunity investment.</p>',0.00,0.01,80.00,20.00,50000.00,50000.00,0.00,53125.00,1.00,0.00,'COMPLETE'),(8,'2018-06-17 00:00:00','Anything New','http://www.ourfood.net.in/','img/portfolio/of.png','<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<style type=\"text/css\">\r\np.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 14.0px; font: 11.0px \'Avenir Next\'; color: #5e5e5e; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000}\r\nspan.s1 {font-kerning: none}\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><h6><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">A private market place for bulk buyers to procure pre-processed quality produce at large scale and a direct sales channel for large Indian micro-farming community. Micro farmer adoption and engagement through two layered agri-business storage center franchises as supply hubs with micro processing farmer franchises as spokes. A software that supports supply chain process automation and real-time price quotes.</span></h6>','Bala','<p>Working with a large corporate partner in setting up franchises across the country&nbsp;</p>','','Agriculture, Supply Chain, Franchise','Hyderabad, India','1 of 2','Krishna Kunapuli, Bala Reddy','','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Our Food has built two AgriBusiness Centers(ABC) close to high crop yield regions, contain inexpensive processing machines, storage, grading and machine training facilities. Each “AgriBusiness Center” issues up-to 50 ”Farmer Franchise” memberships at a fee to progressive farmers with in a 10km proximity to an ABC. Each “Farmer Franchise” collects produce from 100-120 micro-farmers (1-5 Acres land holding), use inexpensive processing equipment to create early value addition as per retailer specification, ship the processed produce to Agro Business Centers. Our Food offers market-ready, reliable, and quality produce to large retail chains. Through technology, company ensures order/inventory management, real-time price quotes, route optimization for large retailers and micro farmers. </span></h6>','<p>OurFood attended 3Lines India Accelerator Program organized by Jindal, UPL, Tata Steel and ANEW Holdings. </p>',0.00,3.33,0.00,0.00,100000.00,100000.00,0.00,0.00,1.00,0.00,'COMPLETE'),(9,'2018-06-17 22:08:55','OverWatchID','https://overwatchid.com/','img/portfolio/ow.png','<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<style type=\"text/css\">\r\np.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; text-align: center; font: 18.0px \'Trebuchet MS\'; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000}\r\nspan.s1 {font-kerning: none; font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures}\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><h6 style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">OverWatchID helps organizations prevent data breaches with its holistic Identity Security Platform, sealing off the most vulnerable points of attack. </span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">By combining and extending all critical identity security technologies into a single platform, OverWatchID delivers a complete and cost-effective solution that’s fast to deploy and easy to manage.</span></h6>','Andy Funk, Cameron Williams, Bob Brenner, Scott Merkle','','','Cybersecurity, Enterprise, SaaS','Denver, CO','0 of 3','','','<h6><font style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;; background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">OverWatchID (OWID)</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">is solving the Identity Security crisis that is impacting business customers across the globe.&nbsp;OWID has developed an integrated, patent-pending SaaS platform that includes four main security tools: Identity Access Management, Multi-Factor Authentication, Privileged Access Management, and Cloud Access Security Brokering. These tools together provide protection for individual usernames and passwords, multiple layers of identity authentication, sensitive account access, and access to cloud-based data.</span></font><span style=\"font-family: Verdana; background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);\">The company provides the industry’s first multi-tenant Identity Security platform that secures the users and all associated 1) systems, 2) devices and 3) applications that these users need to access globally, 24 hours per day. The OverWatchID platform saves customers time, reduces costs and headcount, and protects the organization better than the fragmented systems available in the market today.</span><br></h6>','<div style=\"font-family: Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif, serif, EmojiFont;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana; background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);\">OverWatchID has an impressive executive team with venture-backed and exit experience. CEO Andy Funk was the 6th employee and spent 14 years with Virtela, which was acquired by NTT for $525 Million. Cameron Williams also spent 8 years at Virtela, building up the Security Operations team, Security products, and building up security revenue practice at Virtela from $0 to &gt;$40 Million per year. Scott Merkle led channels for Apropos technology when it went public in 2000, reaching a $600M market cap in its first months of trading. Scott subsequently helped Chris Gladwin found Cleversafe, and was on the advisory board 10 years later when it sold to IBM for $1.4B.</span><br></div>',0.00,20.00,0.00,80.00,50000.00,50000.00,0.00,50000.00,1.00,0.00,'COMPLETE'),(10,'2018-06-17 22:08:55','Sopris Health','https://www.soprishealth.com/','img/portfolio/sh.png','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Sopris Health, an intelligent clinical operations platform, offers a pioneering A.I. medical scribe technology to tackle clinical inefficiencies. The new app, now available on iOS to U.S. physicians and healthcare providers, </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Verdana;\">proved to save time for physicians and reduce the stress of dictation</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">, while making more time available to speak with patients.</span></h6>','Patrick Leonard, John Froelich, Aaron Schram, Laura Pionek','','','AI, SaaS, MedTech','Denver, CO','0 of 3','Patrick Leonard','','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Physicians currently spend 50% of their time doing data entry into health records systems and only<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">12% of their time with patients. The human and remote medical scribe market is large and<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">growing, but most practices and hospitals can\'t afford to employ people to do data entry for<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">physicians. There are 20,000 human scribes in the US, projected to be 100,000 by 2020. The<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">average cost of a scribe is over $41,000 per doctor per year. Listen.MD provides an intelligent<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Digital Scribe to reduce physician data entry for a fraction of what they generally pay today. By<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">reducing data entry burdens, physicians and hospitals have the opportunity to see increased<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">revenues, reduced physician burnout, and focused personal interaction which leads to improved<br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">patient satisfaction.</span></h6>','',0.00,0.00,0.00,0.00,50000.00,0.00,0.00,50000.00,1.00,0.00,'COMPLETE'),(11,'2018-06-17 22:08:55','Bitsbox','https://bitsbox.com/','img/portfolio/bb.png','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">With Bitsbox, children learn to program by creating fun apps that work on computers and gadgets like iPads and Android tablets. The Bitsbox.com website provides each child with a virtual tablet and a place to type their code. The experience starts with lots of guidance, first showing learners exactly what to type, then quickly encouraging them to modify and expand their apps by typing in new commands.</span></h6>','Scott Lininger, Aidan Chopra','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Risk One: Competitors</span><br><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">There are many startups in the kids coding space right now. Though we know that our solution is very different from any of them, explaining those differences to non-coders is challenging. And free options like code.org could eventually expand into the “real coding” area that we are unique in today. MITIGATION: We are positioning ourselves as complimentary to all of these competitors.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Risk Two: Difficult Expansion into School Market</span><br><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Selling into schools is incredibly hard. Sales cycles are long and short-term contract sizes are usually small. It takes years to build up a nice business there. MITIGATION: Sell to consumers first, and always make sure the home-sales business can keep us afloat.</span><br><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\"> <br></span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Risk Three: Team Longevity</span><br><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">We have an incredibly talented team: one that is used to making much more money than we are able to pay them right now. At the moment morale and dedication is high, but we worry that other opportunities would lure them away. MITIGATION: We have generous stock options plans and are dedicated to raising salaries as we can. Everyone on the team has visibility into the financials. The sooner we pull together to reach our revenue milestones, the sooner everyone gets paid more.</span></h6>','','Education, SaaS','Boulder, CO','0 of 3','','','<p>Bitsbox provides a monthly subscription product designed to teach kids how to code. Bitsbox is</p><p>focusing on families with kids ages 5 to 12 with a B2C, direct-to-consumer model. To date, Bitsbox</p><p>has been selling about 99% of their products directly through their website targeting parents of</p><p>children interested in coding or parents who would like to get their children early exposure to</p><p>coding/STEM education at home. They also have a presence in school districts around the US which</p><p>accounts for about 4% of total revenue while the other 96% comes directly from consumers. In</p><p>2018, Bitsbox plans to target more schools to aid additional growth.</p><p>Currently, Bitsbox has 90k permanent coding accounts on their platform (50k in 2016) and 7,600</p><p>paying subscribers in 2018 compared to 2,000 at the time of the last investment round in October</p><p>2016. Bitsbox’s global footprint continues to grow, now having consumers located in 72 countries</p><p>throughout the world. Although the company has expanded into 12 new countries since 2016, 92%</p><p>of sales revenue comes from the US with about 48% of Bitsbox product usage coming from girls. A</p><p>growing user base has led to monthly recurring revenue increasing from $70k in October 2016 to</p><p>$200k in 2017.</p>','<p>AMAZON OPPORTUNITY</p><p>Amazon launched a pilot program in July 2017 with a select group of sellers to offer physical</p><p>subscription boxes. Amazon is extending their Amazon Subscriptions Program to additional</p><p>subscription box sellers, with a full launch planned for Q3 2018. The site’s Subscription Program</p><p>homepage is active, but currently options are limited . According the Bitsbox team, Amazon is</p><p>1</p><p>making a push to gain 15% of the Subscription Box economy.</p><p>Bitsbox does not currently have a formal, signed contract with Amazon to be a part of the service,</p><p>but Amazon has indicated significant interest in having the company be a merchant on their site as</p><p>part of their Subscription Box program. RVC was provided documentation of written</p><p>correspondence between Bitsbox and Amazon, along with meeting minutes from several meetings</p><p>leading up to Amazon’s visit to the Bitsbox team in January 2018.</p><p>Amazon sent a due diligence team to meet with Bitsbox at their offices in Boulder in January to</p><p>identify if Bitsbox’s operating and logistics systems could sustain up to 1000 new subscriptions per</p><p>month. Amazon determined Bitsbox could handle this capacity and have invited them to be a part</p><p>of their 2H 2018 launch through Amazon Prime. Although unknown at this time, it is estimated that</p><p>Bitsbox will launch alongside 50 to 100 other Subscription Box offerings on Amazon. Bitsbox</p><p>anticipates that Amazon will leverage their PR engine to tell the Bitsbox story to Amazon</p><p>customers, helping to set them apart from the crowd. Bitsbox does anticipate that competitor</p><p>Subscription Box companies targeting kids in the same age range will also be a part of the launch,</p><p>including Kiwi Co. and Little Passports. Amazon’s current Subscription Box homepage features</p><p>STEM Club, an Amazon-sponsored subscription program that delivers a new Science, Technology,</p><p>Engineering, and Math themed toy or game to a child/parent every one, two, or three months at a</p><p>price of $19.99 per box, plus tax. See the Competition section below for more details on STEM</p><p>Club.</p><p>Bitsbox subscriptions will be purchased through Amazon upon launch. Bitsbox estimates that</p><p>pricing will remain equal to that of their own site. The process for transacting these new customers</p><p>will involve a daily data dump of new subscribers from Amazon, followed by Bitsbox passing those</p><p>orders on to their fulfillment partner, Thill Inc . Thill is a 3rd-party logistics provider (3PL) based in</p><p>2&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;\">Neenah, Wisconsin. Amazon will then provide a revenue share payment to Bitsbox.</span></p>',0.00,0.04,80.00,20.00,50000.00,50000.00,0.00,50000.00,1.00,0.00,'COMPLETE'),(12,'2018-06-17 22:08:55','CaliberMind','https://www.calibermind.com/','img/portfolio/cm.png','<h6><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">CaliberMind is trusted by mid-market marketing organizations to deliver on their top marketing objectives. CaliberMind does this by enabling their customers to organize, optimize, and activate their data. This leads to to better demand generation results, improved by ABM performance, better marketing analytics and deeper insight their customers\' target market.</span></h6>','Raviv Turner, Oren Zamir','','','Marketing, AI, Software, ERP','Boulder, CO','','','','','<div style=\"font-family: Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><b>Conversation with&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.9987818624970703\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">Raviv</span>\'s</b></span></font><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><b>:&nbsp;</b></span></font></div><div style=\"font-family: Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><font face=\"Calibri,Helvetica,sans-serif,Helvetica,EmojiFont,Apple Color Emoji,Segoe UI Emoji,NotoColorEmoji,Segoe UI Symbol,Android Emoji,EmojiSymbols\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Customers are liking the product&nbsp;that itself is a proof of AI&nbsp;</span></font><font face=\"Calibri,Helvetica,sans-serif,Helvetica,EmojiFont,Apple Color Emoji,Segoe UI Emoji,NotoColorEmoji,Segoe UI Symbol,Android Emoji,EmojiSymbols\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">effectiveness.&nbsp;</span></font><font face=\"Calibri,Helvetica,sans-serif,Helvetica,EmojiFont,Apple Color Emoji,Segoe UI Emoji,NotoColorEmoji,Segoe UI Symbol,Android Emoji,EmojiSymbols\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></font><br></div><div style=\"font-family: Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">New Venture Partners(NVP) signed 500k&nbsp;</span></font><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">in this round &nbsp;and&nbsp;</span></font><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">mandated them to have a sales office in New Jersey area.</span></font><br></div><div style=\"font-family: Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Significant amount of money goes to Sales from this round.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div style=\"font-family: Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><font size=\"2\">