target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(38, 171, 210);\">iTech Solutions</a>&nbsp;–&nbsp;a National<span style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\">&nbsp;staffing firm</span></li></ul><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"><br style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\"></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"></p></div><div class=\"x_update-html-section\" style=\"color: rgb(74, 75, 77); font-family: Whitney, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, serif, EmojiFont;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT:&nbsp;</b><br style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\">The Development Team at&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.7267046363302467\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>&nbsp;has delivered some impressive upgrades to The Platform. Clients now have the ability to use the&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.4246908835078165\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>&nbsp;API’s in a secure mechanism to integrate with any homegrown systems they may have. This is a differentiator between&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.35874112455822904\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>&nbsp;and our competitors and eases sales conversations about converting from legacy systems at the client site to a full-blown&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.5523546480377941\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>implementation.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\">The team has also completed several User and Gateway Agent upgrades. These include a streamlined auto-update process, ability to access logs if the need to troubleshoot the agent ever arises, and the ability to route traffic through the agents. This will allow&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.8112451587383209\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>&nbsp;to support our Identity and Access Management (IAM) implementations and access clients LDAP/AD without having to expose those environments to the Internet. The team has also expanded Cloud Access Security Brokering (CASB) capabilities by building access capabilities to several new WebUI connections that our clients have requested.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\">In the near term, the team will focus efforts on furthering our IAM capabilities, expanding Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) capabilities to include a Web SDK, and supporting the rollout latest updates to the&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.7421831504930549\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>&nbsp;Mobile App and Windows Credential Provider.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\"><b style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 0px;\">STAFFING &amp; TEAM:&nbsp;</b><br></p></div><div class=\"x_update-html-section\" style=\"color: rgb(74, 75, 77); font-family: Whitney, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, serif, EmojiFont; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\">&nbsp;The team is pleased to have two new resources join our Philippines team. Mac Valmore, a mobile application developer, and Ross Castroverde, a developer with expertise in python, have made an immediate impact. Mac will be leading enhancements to the IOS and Android versions of the mobile application, while Ross will continue to enhance the&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.3676642834184327\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>&nbsp;User and Gateway Agent.&nbsp;<br style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\">This past month&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" id=\"0.12231713421945423\" name=\"searchHitInReadingPane\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 238, 148);\">OverWatchID</span>&nbsp;decided to part ways with a single resource. This was not an easy decision, but we feel it was in the best interest of the team to move in a different direction.&nbsp;</p></div>','PUBLISH','March 2018 - Key Stakeholder Update'),(41,11,'2018-02-05','<p><a href=\"http://www.nibletz.com/events/sxswedu/bitsbox\" target=\"_blank\">SXSWedu Preview: Kids Can Easily Code Apps With Bitsbox</a></p><p><a href=\"http://fox17online.com/2018/02/25/grps-teacher-leads-the-way-with-innovation-classroom/\" target=\"_blank\">GRPS teacher leads the way with ‘Innovation Classroom’</a><br><br></p>','PUBLISH','News Links'),(42,2,'2018-05-22','<div id=\"fws_5b35426c4c01a\" data-midnight=\"dark\" data-bg-mobile-hidden=\"\" class=\"wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_row standard_section   \" style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 35px; border: 0px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);\"><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-weight: 600; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px;\">LOUISVILLE, Colo. — May 22, 2018&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2018/05/22/1510236/0/en/Swimlane-Announces-New-Orchestrator-Application-for-the-Palo-Alto-Networks-Application-Framework.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; color: rgb(2, 138, 207); transition: color 0.2s;\">(GLOBE NEWSWIRE)</a><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-weight: 600; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px;\">—&nbsp;</span>Swimlane, a leader in Security Orchestration, Automation and Response, today unveiled its Orchestrator application (app) for the&nbsp;Palo Alto Networks®(NYSE: PANW)&nbsp;Application Framework. Swimlane’s Application Framework Orchestrator app automates the collection of relevant event detail from the Palo Alto Networks Application Framework, delivering critical security event context to SecOps administrators throughout the incident response process.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">Consuming cybersecurity innovations has become an arduous process. Organizations waste time deploying new sensors every time they want to collect a new piece of data and managing point products rather than improving security controls to stay ahead of attackers. The Palo Alto Networks Application Framework makes it easy to add new security capabilities quickly and efficiently. The framework extends the capabilities of the Palo Alto Networks Security Operating Platform, with a suite of APIs that developers can use to connect innovative apps with rich data, threat intelligence and enforcement points. Organizations gain immediate security value from apps developed by an open ecosystem of trusted innovators.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">“Swimlane is committed to helping overburdened security operations teams respond to more alerts faster, and with greater accuracy, by collaborating with Palo Alto Networks. As part of the Palo Alto&nbsp;Networks Application Framework, our customers will have more options for maximizing existing resources and accelerating the incident response process,” said Cody Cornell, founder &amp; CEO of Swimlane.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">Swimlane’s Application Framework Orchestrator app automates the collection of security event data from the Palo Alto Networks Application Framework, and uses it to initiate automated incident response playbooks and to enrich dynamic case management records. This empowers SecOps teams to review more alarms and lower response times, without adding overhead. By automating time-intensive, manual processes and operational workflows and delivering powerful, consolidated analytics, real time dashboards and reporting from across the security infrastructure, Swimlane maximizes the incident response capabilities of over-burdened and understaffed security operations teams.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">“We are delighted to welcome Swimlane to the Palo Alto Networks Application Framework developer community. The framework provides our customers with superior security through cloud-based apps developed by innovative security providers, large and small. Together, we are fueling innovation in the cybersecurity market with apps that are built rapidly, engineered on a common framework, and deliver unique value while solving our customers’ toughest security challenges,” said Lee Klarich, chief product officer of Palo Alto Networks.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-weight: 600; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px;\">AVAILABILITY</span></p><ul style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 30px; border: 0px; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: disc outside;\">Swimlane’s Application Framework Orchestrator app will be available at no charge to all existing Swimlane customers in tandem with the availability of the Palo Alto Networks Application Framework.</li><li style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: disc outside;\">The Palo Alto Networks Application Framework is targeted for availability in August 2018 and will be available worldwide to customers who have purchased either Palo Alto Networks next-generation firewalls or Traps advanced endpoint protection and the Logging Service subscription.</li></ul><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: disc outside;\"><br></p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">About Swimlane</span></p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">Swimlane is a leader in security orchestration, automation and response (SOAR). By automating time-intensive, manual processes and operational workflows and delivering powerful, consolidated analytics, real-time dashboards and reporting from across your security infrastructure, Swimlane maximizes the incident response capabilities of over-burdened and understaffed security operations.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">Swimlane was founded to deliver scalable, innovative and flexible security solutions to organizations struggling with alert fatigue, vendor proliferation and chronic staffing shortages. Swimlane is at the forefront of the growing market for security automation and orchestration solutions that automate and organize security processes in repeatable ways to get the most out of available resources and accelerate incident response. The Swimlane solution offers a broad array of features aimed at helping organizations to address both simple and complex security activities, from prioritizing alerts to remediating threats and improving performance across the entire operation.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">Swimlane is headquartered in Denver, Colorado, with operations throughout North America and Europe. For more information, visit:&nbsp;<a title=\"www.swimlane.com\" href=\"https://www.swimlane.com/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; color: rgb(2, 138, 207); transition: color 0.2s;\">www.swimlane.com</a>.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem;\">About</span><span style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; vertical-align: baseline; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px;\">Palo Alto Networks</span></p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">We are the global cybersecurity leader, known for always challenging the security status quo. Our mission is to protect our way of life in the digital age by preventing successful cyberattacks. This has&nbsp;given us the privilege of safely enabling tens of thousands of organizations and their customers. Our pioneering Security Operating Platform emboldens their digital transformation with continuous&nbsp;innovation that seizes the latest breakthroughs in security, automation, and analytics. By delivering a&nbsp;true platform and empowering a growing ecosystem of change-makers like us, we provide highly&nbsp;effective and innovative cybersecurity across clouds, networks, and mobile devices.</p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 27px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Media Contact</span></p><p style=\"vertical-align: baseline; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">MAPR<br>Melissa Christensen, 720-833-5918<br><a href=\"mailto:mchristensen@mapr.agency\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; color: rgb(2, 138, 207); transition: color 0.2s;\">mchristensen@mapr.agency</a></p></div>','PUBLISH','Swimlane Announces New Orchestrator Application for the Palo Alto Networks Application Framework (5/22)'),(43,4,'2018-04-17','<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(141, 144, 149); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">GOLDEN, Colo. — April 17, 2018 —</span>&nbsp;PharmaJet<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 11.25px; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;\">®</span>, the maker of innovative, needle-free injection technology, today announced that&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.vaccibody.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration-line: underline; color: rgb(87, 160, 209);\">Vaccibody AS</a>&nbsp;has received approval to start their&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.vaccibody.com/vaccibody-as-announces-approval-of-clinical-trial-application-cta-for-its-cancer-neoantigen-phase-i-iia-trial-by-german-regulatory-authorities-paul-ehrlich-institute-pei/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration-line: underline; color: rgb(87, 160, 209);\">cancer neoantigen trial</a>&nbsp;using the PharmaJet Stratis® needle-free injection system.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(141, 144, 149); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Vaccibody, a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company focused on the development of novel immunotherapies, is a leader in the rapidly developing field of individualized therapeutic cancer vaccines targeting solid tumors. In this personalized medicine approach, each patient receives a unique DNA vaccine with up to 20 neoepitopes delivered by the PharmaJet Stratis® needle-free device, in combination with standard of care checkpoint inhibitor therapy. The individualized medicine will be tested in patients with locally advanced or metastatic non-small cell lung cancer, melanoma, renal, bladder or head and neck cancer.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(141, 144, 149); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“We are pleased that Vaccibody has again chosen our PharmaJet Stratis device to deliver their personalized cancer neoantigen vaccine due to its positive effect on their previous DNA based HPV vaccine candidate,” said Ron Lowy, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, PharmaJet Inc. “We continue to be proud to be part of the pharmaceutical industry’s focus on treating multiple types of cancer. This is another example of how our needle-free devices are helping novel DNA technologies move successfully from pre-clinical studies into early and late stage clinical trials.”</p>','PUBLISH','Vaccibody moving forward with Cancer Neoantigen Vaccine Trial'),(44,10,'2018-05-01','<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">DENVER–(BUSINESS WIRE)–May 1, 2018–</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Sopris Health, an intelligent clinical operations platform, today launched a pioneering A.I. medical scribe technology by the same name to tackle clinical inefficiencies. The new app, now&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.soprishealth.com%2F&amp;esheet=51798339&amp;newsitemid=20180501005673&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=available+on+iOS&amp;index=1&amp;md5=749eaa8fc4d9ee368dff6dc2ea93bad3\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(237, 33, 36); word-wrap: break-word;\">available on iOS</a>&nbsp;to U.S. physicians and healthcare providers, proved to save time for physicians and reduce the stress of dictation, while making more time available to speak with patients.</p><p id=\"news-body-cta\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">This press release features multimedia. View the full release here:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180501005673/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(237, 33, 36); word-wrap: break-word;\">https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180501005673/en/</a></p><div id=\"bwbodyimg\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; width: 359px; float: left; padding: 0px 20px 0px 0px;\"><img alt=\"Sopris Health, an intelligent clinical operations platform, offers a pioneering A.I. medical scribe  ... \" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/mms.businesswire.com/media/20180501005673/en/654929/4/Sopris+Health+51798339.jpg?strip=all&amp;ssl=1\" width=\"339\" height=\"453\" style=\"border: 0px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em;\"></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; font-size: 13.6px;\">Sopris Health, an intelligent clinical operations platform, offers a pioneering A.I. medical scribe technology to tackle clinical inefficiencies. The new app, now available on iOS to U.S. physicians and healthcare providers, proved to save time for physicians and reduce the stress of dictation, while making more time available to speak with patients. (Photo: Business Wire)</p></div><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">U.S. physicians spend 50 percent of their time on administration and dictation, and just 27 percent of their time seeing patients, according to a 2016 report in the&nbsp;<i>Annals of Internal Medicine.</i></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">“Traditional dictation and transcription offerings still require a large amount of physician time and attention, often including nights and weekends. Physicians and providers want the experience of a scribe assistant without the cost of hiring a new person,” said Patrick Leonard, CEO and co-founder, Sopris Health. “We believe in pushing technology into the background so that physicians can focus on patient care.”</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">With a vision to slash healthcare costs and increase access, Sopris Health was founded in 2015 taking aim at two major needs: Reducing physician documentation time and generating clinical workflow efficiencies.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Sopris Health completed a substantial beta project in 2017 to establish its artificial-intelligence platform and lay an unparalleled foundation for clinical efficiencies desperately needed in clinics around the nation.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">“We work closely with a variety of partner organizations seeking to immediately improve experiences for their clinical teams, to better serve their patients and communities, and to ultimately, bend the cost of healthcare toward sustainability,” said Mr. Leonard. “Our healthcare system — and the physicians and healthcare professionals who power it — need reliable, secure solutions that increase physical and cognitive space to care for our aging and changing population.”</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\"><span class=\"bwuline\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">How It Works</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">When commissioned by the physician, the Sopris Health app uses secure, artificial intelligence listening during patient visits to capture key information and create an industry-standard SOAP note.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">“Physicians care greatly about innovative solutions that deliver more time with patients, reduce stress, and help to streamline the day-to-day,” said Dr. John Froelich, Sopris Health co-founder, chief medical officer and practicing orthopedic surgeon. “We are passionate about and dedicated to delivering innovative, intelligent solutions that empower providers, allowing them to focus on their patients, not their paperwork.”</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">The patent-pending machine learning technology created by Sopris Health empowers healthcare professionals to perform at their highest level by improving their clinical efficiencies.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\"><span class=\"bwuline\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Solving for Needed Outcomes</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">The Sopris Health team features a wealth of field experience from former Aetna executives to veteran health tech experts to practicing physicians and clinical operations directors. The team works daily to provide true, meaningful improvements to the way healthcare professionals think about and patients experience healthcare.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">The outcomes experienced with Sopris Health include:</p><ul style=\"margin: 25px 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\"><li class=\"bwlistitemmargb\" style=\"list-style-type: none; margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">&nbsp;Significant time savings</li><li class=\"bwlistitemmargb\" style=\"list-style-type: none; margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">&nbsp;Cost efficiencies over alternatives</li><li class=\"bwlistitemmargb\" style=\"list-style-type: none; margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">&nbsp;A reduced level of administrative / workflow requirements on the provider</li><li class=\"bwlistitemmargb\" style=\"list-style-type: none; margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">&nbsp;“Cognitive unload” process</li><li class=\"bwlistitemmargb\" style=\"list-style-type: none; margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">&nbsp;Diminished levels of provider burnout due to decreased documentation burden</li></ul><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">In addition to the outcomes focus, Sopris Health weighs heavily a positive digital user experience, as well as “white glove” customer service experience.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">“We work with medical practices to onboard their provider and administrative teams quickly and effectively,” said Laura Pionek, vice president of product and user experience, Sopris Health. “Additionally, we work with channel partners to provide our technology to their individual members and work with technology partners to connect the provider and patient experiences.”</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">For more information on Sopris Health, visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.canpyadvisory.com&amp;esheet=51798339&amp;newsitemid=20180501005673&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=www.SoprisHealth.com&amp;index=2&amp;md5=e99e7d5f49b22f6df6195c565af0f39b\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(237, 33, 36); word-wrap: break-word;\">www.SoprisHealth.com</a>.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\"><span class=\"bwuline\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">About Sopris Health</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2em; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Denver-based Sopris Health is an intelligent clinical operations platform featuring a pioneering medical scribe technology that reduces providers’ administrative burden, creates more time for patients, and relatedly, decreases the level of physician burnout. Founded in 2015 and unveiled in May 2018, Sopris Health has the dual goals of eliminating physician documentation and automating clinical operations to slash healthcare costs and increase access. Its patent-pending machine learning technology dramatically reduces physician data entry by listening to the physician speak with patients and automatically writing visit notes. This initial product offering is the company’s first step in building the industry’s first intelligent clinical operations platform. For more information on Sopris Health, please visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.soprishealth.com&amp;esheet=51798339&amp;newsitemid=20180501005673&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=SoprisHealth.com&amp;index=3&amp;md5=443164c029016c4dae067e240cf255cb\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(237, 33, 36); word-wrap: break-word;\">SoprisHealth.com</a>&nbsp;or @SoprisHealth on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FSoprisHealth%2F&amp;esheet=51798339&amp;newsitemid=20180501005673&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Facebook&amp;index=4&amp;md5=3c1428d5157a610cdb4a88fdce6b4da1\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(237, 33, 36); word-wrap: break-word;\">Facebook</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsoprishealth&amp;esheet=51798339&amp;newsitemid=20180501005673&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Twitter&amp;index=5&amp;md5=6a1df814cff31d0b7bb1ac80f84ba9d0\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(237, 33, 36); word-wrap: break-word;\">Twitter</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fcompany%2Fsopris-health%2F&amp;esheet=51798339&amp;newsitemid=20180501005673&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=LinkedIn&amp;index=6&amp;md5=30c450adc3ecedce25e64278ca4a6b35\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(237, 33, 36); word-wrap: break-word;\">LinkedIn</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fsopris_health%2F&amp;esheet=51798339&amp;newsitemid=20180501005